<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="159" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,258,499]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,294,319]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Comments.</emphasis>
The specimens were found exclusively in freshwater and slow-flowing lotic environments up to 
<quantity box="[151,222,331,355]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9799999999999995" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" unit="m" value="398.0">398 m</quantity>
asl. The first record of this species for 
<collectingCountry box="[662,745,330,355]" name="Tunisia" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
is reported by Gadeau de 
<bibRefCitation author="Kerville" box="[1041,1214,330,355]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" refString="Gadeau de Kerville, H. (1908) Hemipteres. In: Gadeau de Kerville, H. (Ed.), Voyage zoologique en Khroumirie (Tunisie). Mai- Juin 1906. J. B. Bailliere et fils, Paris, pp. 77 - 85." type="book chapter" year="1908">
Kerville (
<number box="[1148,1206,331,355]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" value="1908.0">1908</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1353,1436,330,355]" name="Tunisia" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
(Tabarka, Jendouba).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="159" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,258,499]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,402,427]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species is distributed in most of European countries, North Africa, 
<collectingCountry box="[1161,1260,402,427]" name="Turkey" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
, Transcaucasia, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,199,439,462]" name="Iran" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Iran</collectingCountry>
, central Asia, and Siberia (
<bibRefCitation author="Jansson" box="[518,678,438,463]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" refString="Jansson, A. (1986) The Corixidae (Heteroptera) of Europe and some adjacent regions. Acta Entomologica Fennica, 52, 1 - 93." type="journal article" year="1986">
